profile_data.summary:
Hi there! I’m Shreya Priya, a Computer Science professional with expertise in Machine Learning, Deep Learning, Computer Vision, and Robotics. With a Master’s in Computer Science from Stony Brook University, I’ve developed algorithms for autonomous systems and real-time object detection, applying my skills to solve complex, real-world problems.

Currently, I’m a Junior Research Fellow at IISER Bhopal, where I’ve been working on a multi-drone path planning algorithm to improve route efficiency. My journey has allowed me to contribute to both academic research and practical applications in autonomous vehicles and aerial robotics.

Recently, I had the opportunity to participate in the McCity AV Challenge, where my team placed 2nd in Trajectory Completion and 5th overall. This challenge allowed us to focus on designing an AV decision-making module that balances safety, efficiency, and comfort.

If you’re interested in discussing innovative advancements in technology or exploring potential collaborations, feel free to connect!

shreya700@gmail.com

projects.description:
Cryo-EM is currently a widely used method for protein structure determination, which aims to determine the structure of 3D specimens from multiple 2D projections. The whole pipeline includes data simulation, particle detection/segmentation in cryo-EM images, 3D reconstruction, and etc. We have a new interdisciplinary research project in which we plan to apply modern machine/deep learning techniques to support a cryo-EM framework. There are several possible research activities related to the various areas of interest in the project that may benefit from machine learning.
As part of the project, I am Researching Machine Learning techniques for particle detection and classification in cryogenic electron microscopy imaging.
projects.title: Cryo-EM
